   <text type="letter">
      <body>
         
               <opener>
                  <dateline rend="right">
                     <date when="1860-08-16">Friday morning, March 2, '60.</date>
                  </dateline>
               </opener>
               <p>Your "Atlantic" has, either in type or MS. an article of mine, sent on by E. H. House<ptr target="prc.00003_n1"/>, and accepted by Mr. Lowell<ptr target="prc.00003_n2"/>&#8212;price $40. In lieu of that sum when the piece is printed, could you enclose me $30 immediately on receiving this, and send by mail&#8212;considering this a receipt in full?</p>
               <closer rend="right">
                  <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
                  <dateline rend="right">
                     <name type="place">Portland av. next to Myrtle | Brooklyn, N. Y.</name>
                  </dateline>
               </closer>
            
            <postscript>
               <p>You will first inquire of Mr. L. about the article, lest I am entertaining some misunderstanding about it.<ptr target="prc.00003_n3"/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
         
      </body>
   </text>
